<br>
I find people that go ballistic at the mere mention of God to be overly sensitive about their philosophical position, because they are looking for a fight, and/or because they want to draw attention to their (non)-beliefs.  Freedom of religion and tolerance also means tolerating those who DO have religion.  I do not go crazy or feel oppressed by the government if I see a Star of David or statue of Buddha in public view.  I do get nervous when Jehova's Witness's come to my door, or Church's throw Bibles at me if I don't handle a snake just right, but that is not oppression, and thus, not against the law. <p>Wyvern Wyrmsong <br>
