<br>
As for certain authority figures banning the display of our flag; I say fight them.  Don't simply let the apologist and neo-communists win and shame you into being embarassed of your flag.  Their viewpoint will be a minority one; raise hell over it and remind them that in the US, everyone gets a vote.  It's so typical that a &quot;sensitive liberal&quot; would be so comfortable forcing their political agenda on those over whom they have power.  After all, isn't that the hallmark behavior of a communist regime?  They are afraid that someone might be &quot;offended&quot; by the flag so they crush YOUR personal right to display it.  <br>
<br>
I would advise anyone offended by the flag to either:<br>
<br>
1) return to a place that flies a flag they are proud of<br>
2) buy some land somewhere outside the US, build a commune, and actually PRACTICE what they preach<br>
3) realize that they are IN THE USA and deal with it<br>
<br>
Name ONE other country where an assinine issue like this is even possible.  Where the concern over &quot;sensitivity&quot; has gotten so extreme that it is ok to impinge on someone's liberties in an effort to spare the feelings of the anti-establishment.  The ironic thing is, that these people would probably swell with pride and cheer if they saw someone flying the flag of some other nation...<br>
